<DOC><DOCNO> AP900211-0017 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-02-11-90 1136EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Italy-Quake     02-11 0144</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Italy-Quake,0147</SECOND><HEAD>Tremor Shakes Turin; No Injuries or Major Damage</HEAD><DATELINE>TURIN, Italy (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A sharp earthquake jolted this northernindustrial city Sunday morning, causing some panic but nocasualties or serious damage.   The tremor, which occurred at 8 a.m., registered 4.2 on theRichter scale and had its epicenter just west of the city,seismologists said.   The quake cut electricity for about a minute throughout Turin,set off car and burglar alarms and sent many residents rushing outof their houses. Police and fire department switchboards wereflooded with calls from alarmed citizens.   Authorities said a few old buildings suffered cracks, but nomajor damage was reported.   A quake of magnitude 4 on the Richter scale can cause moderatedamage. The scale is a gauge of the energy released by anearthquake, as measured by the ground motion recorded on aseismograph.</TEXT></DOC>